An '''epiphyllous lichen''' ("epi" = "above", "phyllous" = "leaf"), or '''foliicolous lichen''' is a [[lichen]] that uses a leaf as its substrate.<ref name=UNOLP>[http://www.unomaha.edu/lichens/Bio%204350%20PDF/Photobionts.pdf Lichen Photobionts, University of Nebraska Omaha] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006145803/http://www.unomaha.edu/lichens/Bio%204350%20PDF/Photobionts.pdf |date=2014-10-06 }}</ref> [[Chlorophyta]] are common [[photosynthetic]] partners [[phycobiont]]s of epiphyllous lichens.<ref name=UNOLP/>

